Package it.unipr.sowide.actodes.interaction

Provides classes and interfaces defining some message contents used in the basic interactions between actors. In particular, it contains the classes defining the requests used for forcing the life-cycle of other actors and for having their information.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Inform
    The Inform interface defines the content of a message used for informing somebody about a specific fact.
    Request
    The Request interface defines the content of a request message.
    Response
    The Response interface defines the content of a response message.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Become
    The Become class defines a request asking an actor to move to another behavior.
    Create
    The Create class defines a request asking an actor or an actor space service provider to create a new actor.
    Forward
    The Forward class defines a request asking anactor to forward a message to another actor.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Done
    The Done enumeration is used for informing about the successful execution of a request when the execution of such a task does not produce data.
    Error
    The Error enumeration defines the most common errors that can happen during the interaction between actors and that are used for informing about the failure of the delivery of messages.
    Kill
    The Kill enumeration defines a request asking an actor to kill itself.
    Lock
    The Lock enumeration defines a request asking an actor to start its exclusive service.
    Save
    The Save enumeration defines a request asking an actor to make a persistent copy of its state.
    Start
    The Start enumeration defines a request asking an actor to start itself.
    Status
    The Status enumeration defines action for informing the receiver that the sender is alive or informing that either is stopping itself, or is killing itself.
    Stop
    The Stop enumeration defines an action used for asking an actor for stopping itself.
    Unlock
    The Unlock enumeration defines an action used for asking an actor to end its exclusive service.
